ovember 28, 1957", "width": 5058}, {"fulltext_service": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_hamlet_ver01/data/sn84025909/00542865301/1957112801/0471.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "mimetype": "text/plain", "use": "text"}], "pagination": {"current": 4, "first": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1", "from": 4, "last": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=6", "next": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=5", "of": 8, "page_list": [{"number": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, {"number": 2, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=2"}, {"number": 3, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=3"}, {"number": 4, "url": null}, {"number": 5, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=5"}, {"number": 6, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=6"}], "perpage": 1, "perpage_options": [25, 50, 100, 150], "previous": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-28/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=3", "results": "4 - 4", "to": 4, "total": 8}, "previous_resource": {"label": "Previous Issue", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84025909/1957-11-21/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, "related_items": [{"access_restricted": true, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/86707352/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/86707352/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/86707352/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/coll/item/86707352/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/coll/item/86707352/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/86707352"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["frances benjamin johnston photograph collection (library of congress)", "johnston, frances benjamin"], "date": "1903", "dates": ["1903"], "description": ["301 photoprints : 257 gelatin silver, 44 cyanotype ; 23 x 28 cm. or smaller. | State fair in Saint Paul, Minn., including parents and children, booths, rides, and health exhibit. Locomotive; steamboat with people standing on landing; group attending unidentified ceremony; black women posed for portrait; church in Saint Paul. Horse farm, arches in Palo Alto, Calif.--probably on Stanford University campus. Landscapes and train at Mt. Tamalpais, Calif.; sea lions on beach, dwellings, and store windows in Calif. San Francisco Chinatown. Boats on Columbia River, Washington. Yellowstone National Park landscapes, including geysers, rivers, canyons, frost-covered trees; Park tour showing teamsters, wagons, stagecoaches, camping party, tourists--including Johnston--and guides."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-03-07T13:35:42.285Z", "group": ["coll", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "groups-of-images", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/86707352/", "image_url": ["https://www.loc.gov/static/images/original-format/group-of-images.svg"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["washington", "california", "columbia river", "chinatown", "united states", "tamalpais", "saint paul", "san francisco", "palo alto", "mount", "yellowstone national park", "minnesota", "wyoming"], "mime_type": ["image/jpg"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/86707352", "2021-10-19t13:14:32", "86707352", "http://www.loc.gov/item/11510945"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["lot 11739", "catalog", "prints and photographs division", "groups of images (lots)"], "score": 24.981905, "shelf_id": "LOT 11739 (G) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["johnston, frances benjamin", "cyanotypes", "rivers", "columbia river", "washington (state)", "united states", "tourism", "gelatin silver prints", "palo alto (calif.)", "vehicles", "palo alto", "yellowstone national park", "churches", "railroad locomotives", "horse farms", "health education", "w